25\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Sophr.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">125</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; but in <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ pres.\">pres.</a></tns> and <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ impf.\">impf.</a></tns> (which are the tenses most in use), <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">offer to buy, bargain</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">bid</tr_> for a thing, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὄφρ᾽ ἄλλων ὠνῇ κλῆρον</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0020.tlg002.perseus-grc1:341\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hes.\">Hes.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Op.\">Op.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">341</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠνέεσθαι τῶν φορτίων</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">wished to buy</tr_> some of their wares, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">began to bargain</tr_> for them, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hdt.\">Hdt.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.1</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Κροῖσός σφι ὠνεομένοισι ἔδωκε</foreign> gave it them <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">when they offered to buy,</tr_> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:69\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">69</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τὰς νήσους οὐκ ἐβούλοντο ὠνευμένοισι πωλέειν</foreign> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:165\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">165</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:139\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope 